# Shell scripts must keep LF line endings so they run on the Linux deploy
# target. A CRLF shebang (`#!/bin/bash\r`) makes the kernel look for the
# interpreter "/bin/bash\r", which doesn't exist, and the container
# crash-loops with "exec docker-entrypoint.sh: no such file or directory".
#
# Needed because `git archive` (used by .ops/sync_and_up.py-style deploys)
# applies core.autocrlf=true conversion on Windows checkouts, rewriting LF
# blobs to CRLF in the produced tarball. `eol=lf` overrides that everywhere.
*.sh text eol=lf
